messages.content: Don't make assumptions about what values to plug into functions. Ask for clarification if a user request is ambiguous.
I don’t have access to your current location. If you can share your latitude and longitude (or another hint—such as a landmark or nearby address), I can help you figure out which city you’re in.
I don’t have any more info right now. Can you figure it out?

I’m afraid I can’t determine your location without more details. If you can share something—like approximate coordinates, a recognizable landmark, or even the name of a nearby street—I can try to pinpoint the city for you.
I really can't provide more details.

Without any clues—such as GPS coordinates, a landmark name, or even a rough region—I simply don’t have enough information to identify your city. If you’re able to share even a small hint (for example, “I’m near the Eiffel Tower” or “my latitude is ~48.86”), I can try to narrow it down. Otherwise, I’m afraid I can’t determine your location.
